<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - TIMING GEAR TRAIN - INSPECTION
        PRIOR TO REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INSPECTION PRIOR TO REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to removing any gear, check the backlash of idler gear and camshaft gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the oil pump drive gear spline and the crankshaft gear for nicks, chips
                    or wear. Replace as necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Idler Gear Backlash (Refer to Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150812">8.12</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount a magnetic base dial bore diameter to the crankcase at a suitable location.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip at a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">"Zero" the dial indicator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the camshaft gear and move the idler gear by hand. Read the indicator and record
                    the backlash.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150801.xml" xrefid="hl4150801">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>, inspect the gear
                    for misassembly or wear. If worn, replace the gear.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Camshaft Gear Backlash (Refer to Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150813">8.13</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a magnetic base dial indicator to the crankcase at a suitable location.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip at a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">"Zero" the dial indicator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the idler gear steady and move the camshaft gear by hand. Read the indicator and
                    record backlash.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150801.xml" xrefid="hl4150801">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>, replace the
                    camshaft gear.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>At this stage of disassembly, it is advantageous to measure camshaft end play, refer to
                            <hotlnk document="e415_E41505.xml" xrefid="e41505">"ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS
                                AND PUSH RODS"</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150812" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11346" filename="../figcg1/CG11346.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.12. Measure Idler Gear Backlash.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150813" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12081" filename="../figcg1/CG12081.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.13. Measure Camshaft Gear Backlash.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
